{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17622133","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17622133"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:00:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:00:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16785"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16785","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16785"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9476"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109886"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9476","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9476"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16785"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92247"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5234"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22406"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23054"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41233"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109886","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109886"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EChemotherapy medications can affect rapidly dividing cells through various mechanisms. Understanding their teratogenic potential is crucial when treating cancer during pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAntimetabolite agents are absolutely contraindicated in the first trimester of pregnancy due to their high risk of causing foetal abnormalities.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the teratogenic mechanism of antimetabolite chemotherapy agents?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Disrupts DNA synthesis during cell division","Triggers maternal immune response","Increases oxidative stress","Inhibits folate metabolism","Blocks microtubule formation"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisruption of DNA synthesis during cell division\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary teratogenic mechanism of antimetabolite chemotherapy agents like methotrexate. These drugs interfere with nucleotide synthesis and DNA replication, which is particularly harmful to rapidly dividing embryonic cells during organogenesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect mechanisms can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETriggers maternal immune response\u003C/strong\u003E: antimetabolites work through direct interference with cell division rather than immune-mediated mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases oxidative stress\u003C/strong\u003E: although oxidative stress may occur as a secondary effect, the main teratogenic mechanism is interference with DNA synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits folate metabolism\u003C/strong\u003E: while some antimetabolites like methotrexate do inhibit folate metabolism, this is a mechanism of action rather than the direct teratogenic mechanism, which is the disruption of DNA synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks microtubule formation\u003C/strong\u003E: this is the mechanism of antimicrotubule agents like vinca alkaloids and taxanes, not antimetabolites, which primarily interfere with DNA synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe risk of teratogenic effects is highest during the first trimester when rapid cell division and differentiation occur during organogenesis. This can result in structural birth defects, growth restriction, or pregnancy loss.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Antimetabolite chemotherapy agents like methotrexate interfere with DNA synthesis and are particularly harmful during early embryonic development.","The first trimester is the most critical period for teratogenic effects due to rapid organogenesis.","Chemotherapy agents can cause spontaneous abortion, birth defects, and developmental delays when administered during pregnancy."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92247"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16785"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92247","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92247"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-27T13:38:44+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-27T13:42:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9476"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109886"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","syn